    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690d.11241/12</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-24">September 24,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 4258</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatches No.
                    9793 of August 27, 1929<note n="59" xml:id="d310fn59">Not printed.</note> and
                    No. 9819 of September 6, 1929, with regard to the customs immunity of American
                    philanthropic and educational institutions in Syria and the Lebanon.</p>
                <p>In view of the fact that the Foreign Office Note of August 22, 1929,<note n="60"
                        xml:id="d310fn60">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_269">p. 269</ref>.</note>
                    enclosed with the despatch first mentioned above, fails to give consideration to
                    the proposal submitted to the French High Commission in Beirut by Mr. Knabenshue
                    on August 30, 1928, the Department <pb facs="0393" n="273" xml:id="pg_273"/>
                    would be glad to have you take opportunity again to express to the Foreign
                    Office the hope that it may be found possible to give further study to Mr.
                    Knabenshue’s proposal.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Trusler Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
